td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Casters Advice Wanted</span><hr size=1> I have been thinking long and hard about possibly making a serious attempt at playing an int caster, most likely a wizard. <br>
<br>
I was hoping that some you out there with a lot of experience in this area might offer me advice on race class combinations and maybe even gear suggestions. I am not rich, somewhat due to a recurring nasty case of philanthropism, but mostly because of laziness. While being poor, I do have access to a druid and a big fat blue tank who has delusions of being both a gnome and a dr00d, so I can go get stuff the old fashioned way too.<br>
<br>
Advice, if you have any to offer, is much appreciated.<br>
<br>
Prybutok Agonista Browneyes<br>
Dazed Delusional Warlord of &lt;Agony&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saalron@vazaellecommunitycenter>Saalron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 638<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/24/02 3:54:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3411.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> info</span><hr size=1> The caps on stats is raising so you should probably consider how high you plan on raising this toon and then picking a race that allows for it's maximization. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerai>Kerai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Teh Anti-American</span><br>  Posts: 3313<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/24/02 4:08:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3411.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.sowned.com/bleh/kerai2.gif height=85 width=66></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: info</span><hr size=1> if you max out the PoP AA for stat enhancement you can potentiatially reach 330 int. 50 from int/wis one (10 per, 5 lvls) and 25 from general for all (5 lvls of 5).<br>
<br>
For Max int Erudite is best. But then their vision sucks, which isnt a crucial fact it is annoying to a) get an item for it b) have to recast infra/ultra on yourself over and over. In Katta it's amazing the difference between reg infra and lich ultravision. And stuff like dreadlands passage from port area to rest is pitch black.<br>
<br>
Stamina is also a stat you want raised. As a wizzie you might Quad or AoE and so the ability to take a few hits and keep going is crucial. You have no self-heal to my knowledge.<br>
<br>
Then there is the deity and racial armors. Inkies and High Elves get some nice cultural. So you might wanna check out EQtraders to see stats on cultural.<br>
<br>
Faction isn't much of an issue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bigemnoseandhow>bigemnose andhow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/24/02 4:30:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3411.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: info</span><hr size=1> If your not wealthy, then there is only one choice in which race to choose for a Wizard.  That choice is Erudite because they have the highest starting INT.  INT is the name of the game when it comes to wizards.  The more INT you have, the more mana you have, and if you don't have mana, then your going to die.  This is particularly noticable at lower levels where you only get enough mana to nuke once or twice before you run out of mana hahhaa...  it helps you progress through the lower levels alot more quickly if you have a high INT because of the ammount of mana you get from it.<br>
<br>
Later on in the game when you start making some money, you will find that it is quite easy to max out your INT with some decent Bazaar bought INT items because you start out with a good INT base as an Erudite.<br>
<br>
Now, that being said, Erudites are the ugliest wizards in the game in my opinion with their massively oversized foreheads.  So, if you got some money for INT gear early on OR you can handle leveling slowly for the first 20 levels, then go with a Gnome Wizard cause the gnomes look freaking awesome!  Besides, there is nothing cooler then watching a 60 level gnome wizard blast the sh!t out of giants and dragons.  It's just cool watching a migit unleash massive raw energy on big oversized beasts Mahaha...<br>
<br>
And if you want the best looking wizard in the game and your willing to put up with prejudice NPC's through out Norath, then go with a Dark Elf wizard.  There is no single better looking wizard in the game then the Dark Elf.  The Dark Elf Wizard is the $$$ of cool looking wizards.<br>
